Princess informal settlement reisdents torched a truck, barricading the Albertina Sisulu Road around with burning tyres and rocks. JOHANNESBURG - Police and Johannesburg Metro Police Department (JMPD) officers are monitoring the Princess informal settlement in Roodepoort on Tuesday morning following a night of violent protesting.Protesters torched a truck, barricading the Albertina Sisulu Road with burning tyres and rocks on Monday night.It s unclear what residents are protesting over.JMPD s Wayne Minaar says: Albert Sisulu Road remains closed this morning due to the violent protests last night. A truck was torched and there s still a lot of debris and rocks on that road. It s not safe for motorists to drive past this morning. Motorists will have to use alternative routes. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)